President Muhammadu Buhari has condoled
with family of Pa Adama Aduku, oldest surviving soldier of the Nigerian Army
and World War 11 Veteran, who passed on at 101, describing him as a soldier’s
soldier and an epitome of honour. A
statement by the Special Adviser to the President
(Media &
Publicity) Femi Adesina, on Friday said  the President commiserates with friends
and associates of the war veteran and Kogi State government on the loss,
believing that the virtues of hard work and loyalty to the flag that he lived
for will continue to be promoted. Buhari also commended Aduku’s strong
spirit and commitment to statehood, especially for actively participating in
the 2019 Nigerian Army Day celebration and other activities of the Nigerian
Legion. The President prayed that the almighty
God will receive the soul of the departed, and comfort his family.